metadata.name: DÃ©collage #53
metadata.description:
A generative sketch based on the concept of dÃ©collage, an artistic process that involves cutting or tearing pieces of an original image. The resulting outputs bear a resemblance to artworks produced using the lacerated poster technique, where posters are layered and torn to reveal parts of the posters underneath.

In live mode, add &size=<YOUR_PIXEL_SIZE> to change the pixel size of the image for export (Right click to save). For example, &size=4000 will set the width of the image to be 4000 pixels. Note that this will not work with sizes beyond 5000 pixels.

(Allowlist is based on quantity of previous works owned).

metadata.name: Isola della Scala #74
metadata.description:
All things pass, all things flow,
Movement, connection, separation, all in tow.
A misstep and we're knocked off course,
But in the end, we rise, as if by force.
Like a dance of dominoes, we fall and we stand,
In this ever-changing world, we're a part of the grand.

The name of this work is the name of the city where my roots began, where the path of everything changed and new directions in life were taken.

Made with p5.js, p5.grain and much love

metadata.name: Plottable Art Deco #61
metadata.description:
Initially made for #genuary 2023, JAN. 20 Art Deco prompt, a fxhash generator was generalized. It can yield various properties including x and y mirroring,

Meant to be plotted with a gold gel pen on a A4 dark blue paper.

"Introducing 'Plottable Art Deco', created for #genuary2023's Art Deco prompt. This fxhash generator is capable of producing unique properties such as x and y mirroring and other rare patterns, making every outcome truly one-of-a-kind. Designed to be plotted on A4 dark blue paper with a gold gel pen, this digital NFT is the recipe to a plottable art piece.

Owning this NFT grants the right to plot or request a physical plot from the artist on https://greweb.me/plots/nft

The source code for this piece is available on GitHub at https://github.com/gre/gre/tree/master/doodles/plottable-artdeco, and is licensed under CC BY-SA 4.0.

metadata.name: Splinter #147
metadata.description:
This release marks my first anniversary on the fx(hash) platform! I want to extend a huge thank you to everyone for a fantastic year, and I'm looking forward to many more in the generative-art world!

The basic algorithm is an evolution of the one I used in my first release, Raked Strokes. Instead of mimicking a brush with parallel segments, I'm using perpendicular line segments to define the overall abstract shape and then drawing each line in a simulated media. This approach blends my first attempts at natural media with everything I've learned in the past year.

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press 's' to save a screenshot. The image size is 2357x3000px
Press 'p' to pause/resume during drawing.

Features
- Base path shape: line, circle, diamond, or rectangle
- Elements defining the spacing and orientation of the line segments
- The base path painted in the background
- Monochrome, dark background, and selection of palettes
- Ink pen styling: thickness, quality, and background blocking
- Paint styling: color distribution, quality
- Shapes: triangle, polygons, criteria for insertion
- Shapes overdrawing: outlines or perpendicular segments

Copyright (c) 2022 Matt Perkins, hello@mattperkins.me, @nudoru on Twitter. Licensed under CC BY-NC-SA 4.0, see LICENSE.txt for more information.

metadata.name: MOUNTAINS #213
metadata.description:
"MOUNTAINS" is a work that belongs to the "FLUX Series", which utilizes the same techniques and processes as the previous work "FLUX". The shape in this piece is created by placing elements using noise and then performing recursive pixel operations on these elements.

The inspiration behind this work came from my continued sketches and studies of Flow Field, which led me to discover an expression of objects that seemed to be corroding. I believed that by applying this technique, I could create a realistic and vivid sculpture from a geometric shape.In this work, this corrosion treatment is applied to a geometric triangular shape of overlapping rectangles to form a realistic and dynamic mountain landscape.
It was as if geometric figures like Plato's "ideas" were materialized in the real world.

Additionally,  I was also inspired by the mountain views from my hometown at New Year's and by the manga background paintings of Yoshiharu Tsuge, who specializes in depicting villages with old hot springs.

It is possible to get a 5760 x 3240 px png file by right click save.

Please feel free to contact me if you have any inquiries.

Artwork by hasaqui, @hasaqui.
Made with p5js
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0

metadata.description:
Type-o-Graphic embraces the ethos of David Carson's groundbreaking graphic design work. It explores the intersections of typography, design, art and chance, harnessing the power of randomness to create a series of posters that are a frenetic celebration of typographic chaos.

This collection is intended to be customized and printed. Your initial thumbnail output is only the beginning â€” several parameters are changeable to find a combination and format to your liking. Please use the keys below to explore the thousands of possible variations within each piece.

metadata.name: Fractionary #104
metadata.description:
Fractionary is stunning because it is so straightforward.

When examined closely, one can see the careful planning and attention to detail that have gone into constructing each piece, despite the fact that at first glance it could seem as though the rectangles have been set haphazardly.

The colors have been selected to complement one another, and the placement of each rectangle has been carefully considered to produce a visual equilibrium.

Dazeem Gagaloo, 2023

metadata.name: Espacios comunes #237
metadata.description:
At moment we decide to draw a square on top of a circle, we are defining a time arrow, a third dimension on the 2D plane, where shapes can be on o top of each other, come one after the other. In this project i wanted to remove that time arrow, that third dimension, and leave the 2D plane as flat as possible.

Shapes are not drawn in sequence, they are formed by the continuous addition of points to each region defined by the shapes intersections. Not a single region is on top of the other. They are the result of the combination of shapes, and defined by them. Horizontal, decentralized societies. Espacios comunes. We can see the circles, squares, plane cuts, but we cannot give them an order or authority.

-----

Key controls:

- UP arrow: Increases the sketch resolution. It will take longer to render but it will produce better quality images.
- DOWN arrow: Decreases the sketch resolution.
- f: Removes or adds an empty frame around the image.
- d: Increases the points density. More points will be painted and regions will become more full.
- n: Increases the pixel noise.
- b: Decreases the pixel noise.
- z: Switches on and off the simple pixel sorting algorithm. Move the mouse left and right to change the pixel stickiness.
- x: Switches on and off a more complex version of the pixel sorting algorithm.
- i: Displays some log information.
- p: Pauses the sketch.
- s: Saves a screenshot of the artwork. The image resolution will depend on the sketch resolution, which is controlled by the UP and DOWN arrows.

-----

URL controls:

width=2000 will set the sketch width to 2000 pixels.
proportion=2.3 will set the sketch width-to-height ratio to 2.3.
You can combine these two parameters to create any image output you want. For example, to create an image that is 3000 pixels wide and 5000 pixels high, one just needs to add &width=3000&proportion=0.6 to the URL.

-----

Special thanks to @andregorayeb (Gora) and @ItonkStudio (Itonk) for letting me use some of their color palettes for this project.

metadata.name: Fifty Windows #40
metadata.description:
"Fifty Windows" is a minimal generative art project that explores thoughts and feelings around the theme of life's choices, by symbolically representing the idea of looking through a window to the other side, where there are all the opportunities and life experiences that we could have missed.

But the other side of the window also represent the idea of a gaze that looks out, where one can explore different life experiences and new paths of growth and fulfillment.

The project is also focused on the idea of perspective, that is allowed by the minimalistic tracts of the artworks, that make you understand that youâ€™re in front of a windows, but youâ€™re never sure if you're looking in or out.

Just like in life, sometimes we may be on one side of the window, feeling like we've missed something, while other times we're living something that others may be regretting.

Life is just a game of perspectives.

- - -

To save artworks at high resolution press "s" in live mode and wait :)

metadata.name: Type-o-Graphic #132
metadata.description:
Type-o-Graphic embraces the ethos of David Carson's groundbreaking graphic design work. It explores the intersections of typography, design, art and chance, harnessing the power of randomness to create a series of posters that are a frenetic celebration of typographic chaos.

This collection is intended to be customized and printed. Your initial thumbnail output is only the beginning â€” several parameters are changeable to find a combination and format to your liking. Please use the keys below to explore the thousands of possible variations within each piece.

Features:
B - Toggle border
N - Change border colour
K - Change background colour (if visible)
T - Toggle top finish (if applicable)
Up/Down - Change colour palette (43)
Left/Right - Change blend modes (20)
L - Change to Landscape
P - Change to Portrait
S - Save image

0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5 - Change resolution of image
0 - 600 x 900 - (low-res)
1 - 1200 x 1800 - 4x6" @ 300dpi - (default)
2 - 2400 x 3600 - 8x12" @ 300dpi
3 - 3600 x 5400 â€“ 12x18" @ 300dpi
4 - 4800 x 7200 - 16x24" @ 300dpi
5 - 7200 x 10800 - 24x36" @ 300dpi

See accompanying article for more info:
https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/type-o-graphic

Created with p5js by fauxjebus in 2023

metadata.name: All The Way #9
metadata.description:
"All the Way" is a visually stunning and dynamic generative art piece that is sure to make a striking addition to any art collection. Created using the programming language p5js, this artwork is truly one of a kind and cannot be replicated.

The vibrant colors, fluid shapes, and dynamic movement in "All the Way" make it an ideal centerpiece for any space. The constantly shifting shapes and colors create a sense of energy and motion that will draw the eye and captivate the viewer. This piece is perfect for anyone who loves abstract art or is looking for something unique and eye-catching to add to their collection.

Additionally, the theme of "All the Way" is one that is sure to resonate with many people. The artwork represents the flow of life, the power of creativity, and the endless possibilities that exist in the world around us. This makes it an ideal choice for anyone who values personal growth, exploration, and a sense of adventure.

Whether you're an art collector, an art enthusiast, or simply someone who appreciates beautiful and thought-provoking art, "All the Way" is a must-have addition to your collection. With its dynamic and abstract style, this piece is sure to spark conversations and inspire new ideas. Don't miss out on the chance to own a truly unique and captivating artwork that you will enjoy for years to come!

To save image press "s"
To save image in high quality add &print=2 or &print=3 in the live URL then press "s".

Note: Image can take a minute to render.
